description:
The RX driver wrapper is a nice addition to the Mongo async driver and solves a lot of our problems integrating with RXJava. However we have one problem that is fairly typical: we want to customize on which scheduler events are processed. In our case, this should not occur on a mongo driver thread.

Using the observeOn(), it is fairly easy to schedule the returned observable on a different thread, but it is very verbose and error prone to do this after every invocation to the mongo RX driver. It would be really useful if there would be a common adapter function that could be defined at the MongoCollection or MongoClient level, that would allow adapting all Observables to something else if used. e.g.

interface ObservableAdapter {
Observable<T> adapt(Observable<T>);
}

MongoClient.withObservableAdapter(observable -> observable.observeOn(...));

// any operations that return an observable are now adapted to always run on the custom scheduler
